article.description: — Dzmitry Ryuny registered 16 points as San Francisco easily beat Portland 88-64 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Ryuny leads San Francisco over Portland 88-64
article.linkText: Ryuny leads San Francisco over Portland 88-64
article.story: SAN FRANCISCO -- — Dzmitry Ryuny registered 16 points as San Francisco easily beat Portland 88-64 on Thursday night. Khalil Shabazz had 19 points for San Francisco (8-5, 2-1 West Coast Conference). Damari Milstead added 10 points. San Francisco posted a season-high 24 assists. Meanwhile, the Dons had a season-high 10 blocks. Portland scored 43 points in the first half, a season high for the team. Isiah Dasher had 17 points for the Pilots (6-4, 0-1). Ahmed Ali added 13 points. Eddie Davis had 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
